Metromail Corp said it expectsflat operating profits for its 1987 fiscal year ending May 31with last fiscal year's earnings from operations of 9,943,000dlrs, or 1.05 dlrs a share.    The company said the flat results will be due to higherthan normal expenditures during the fourth quarter forexpansion of its data processing capabilities.    Earlier, Metromail reported fiscal 1987 third quarterearnings of 2.4 mln dlrs, or 25 cts a share, versus three mlndlrs, or 32 cts a share, the prior third quarter, and ninemonths net of 7.2 mln dlrs, or 76 cts a share, versus 7.8 mlndlrs, or 82 cts a share the prior nine months. Reuter&#3;